des:
Connect your GTC Smart Stove App to Alexa in order to conveniently control your Grand Teton Collection Smart Pellet Stove with just your voice!

Connect Alexa to your GTC Smart Pellet Stove in a few simple steps: 
(1) Download our “GTC Smart Stove” app in Google Play or iOS App Store;
(2) Launch the app and register a new account (or log in if you’re already registered);
(3) Turn on your Grand Teton pellet stove and connect with the GTC Smart Stove App;
(4) IMPORTANT: You can rename the pellet stove unit in the GTC Smart Stove App;
(5) Download “Amazon Alexa” app from Amazon Market, Google Play or iOS App Store and connect Echo with “Alexa” app;
(6) Search the Alexa Skills directory for “GTC Smart Stove” skill;
(7) Click Enable skill of GTC Smart Stove App, and you’ll be navigated to GTC Smart Stove login page;
(8) Follow the instructions on the page to complete linking;
(9) Setup is complete and you are now ready to use voice control.

Voice Commands include the following:
“Alexa, turn on/off <device name>.”
“Alexa, what is the temperature of <device name>?”
“Alexa, what is the target temperature of the <device name>?”
“Alexa, set <device name> to [75] degrees.”
